FROM: build the next steps on the image specified
ARGS: arguments you pass through
ENV: specified arguments
RUN: Runs a command at build time (when the image is built)
CMD: Works at container level
COPY copies the specified file on your machine into the container, at build time
WORKDIR: any other commands occur in the specified location
LABEL: the name of the maintainer, the one who owns the docker container
ENTRY POINT: 

You can have multiple RUN's but only one CMD
If you don't specify a version in the FROM then it will run the latest version it can find.

Expose [PORT NUMBER]; doesn't actually do anything but is a note to remind the user what port they 
need to open when running the application.

